  "name": "Arcane Shot: Beguiling Arrow",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/weapons/polearms/spear-ice-crystal-blue.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your Enchantment magic causes this arrow to temporarily beguile its target. The creature hit by the arrow takes an extra <strong>2d6 psychic damage</strong>, and choose one of your allies within 30 feet of the target. The target must succeed on a <strong>Wisdom saving throw</strong>, or it is <strong>Charmed </strong>by the chosen ally until the start of your next turn. This Effect ends early if the chosen ally attacks the Charmed target, deals damage to it, or forces it to make a saving throw.</p>\n<p>The psychic damage increases to <strong>4d6 </strong>when you reach 18th level in this class.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: After adding this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Arcane Shot.</em></p>\n</section>",
